column266: Interesting! I am bothered by the sounds in my neighborhood, but never thought how that would affect our children. It's noise pollution. I am  < 1/2 mi from the following: TAFB, a train station, industrial business park, surrounded by 3 schools (Elementary, Middle and High School) The high school has extracurricular events all year (recess, bells, PE, football games, marching band, track, soccer, graduation) It's impossible to leave our neighborhood during school hours. Gridlock. The sounds in our neighborhood include loud landscaping, barking dogs, the garbage man at 5:55 am and a neighbor several houses down that plays the drums. He recently started a band, lol. Thank you for  the opportunity to participate in your study and for opening my eyes.
